<td valign="top"><img src="http://espresso.ad.ucop.edu:8084/xtf/data/nlm/bmc/figures/1471-2105-6-303-1" />
<br /><span class="gen" id="F1">[Figure ID: </span>F1<span class="gen">] </span></td>
<td valign="top"><span class="label">Figure 1 
				</span><span class="capture-id">
                  <p><b>European population partitions</b>. European population partitions for all 1000 haplotypes are shown. Block algorithms are abbreviated as HB (HapBlock), GA (Gabriel's
                     method), MD (MDBlocks). The first two tracks show resulting block partitions from HapBlock and Gabriel's method using all SNPs. Next set of three tracks display resulting block
                     partitions using all SNPs with a 10% MAF. The shared blocks track shows chromosomal regions common to all three block partitions using SNPs with a 10% MAF. The last two tracks
                     show SNP positions of all SNPs and SNPs with at least a 10% MAF.</p>

               </span><br /></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td valign="top"><img src="http://espresso.ad.ucop.edu:8084/xtf/data/nlm/bmc/figures/1471-2105-6-303-2" />
